modules.description: Provides functions to create and configure fake functions that return specified values or raise exceptions, along with methods to track and inspect their calls. Works with function types and references to track argument patterns and invocation counts. Used in testing to simulate dependencies and verify interactions without real implementation.

Provides functions to create and manage mock objects that simulate behavior for testing. Works with parameterized types for arguments and return values, and side effects like returning values or raising exceptions. Used to verify expected interactions by recording and inspecting call arguments during test execution.
